main event: On June 15, 1963, a bright white object was observed in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object appeared to be about the size of a car,The observation lasted for 11 minutes,The object was initially at 12 degrees elevation and was moving slowly,It was concluded that the object could possibly be a balloon, but definitely not an aircraft or astronomical object,Specific coordinates were noted for the observation with aircraft position at 33-40N 175-00W.
sighted object: one bright white object about the size of a car
